                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td colspan="2" style="padding-top:15px;text-align: justify;" >This is with respect to, obtaining consent from you for the proposed modification of sanctioned plans of the above project. In this regard, please note the following:</td>
                            </tr>
                        </table>
                        
                        <ol >
                            <li><p style="text-align: justify;">With reference to the above Project <strong>“MAHENDRA AARYA”</strong> being developed by us which has been registered with the Karnataka Real Estate Regulatory Authority under the Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Act, 2016 (ACT) and Karnataka Real Estate (Regulation and Development) Rules, 2017 (RULES)on 08/04/2021 vide registration No.PRM/KA/RERA/1251/308/PR/210408/004106.</p></li>
                            <li><p style="text-align: justify;">In view of the provisions of the Act and Rules applicable to the project and in view of the proposed modification, the Development Plan and Sanctioned Building Plan of the Project will be changed by virtue of the modified Development Plan and Sanctioned Building Plan, the Project may include additional lands, with additional Towers and units which will be informed after obtaining the modified plan sanction. Apart from the said modifications, there are no other changes proposed to the Development Plan and Sanctioned Building Plan. </p></li>
                            <li><p style="text-align: justify;">The Development Plan has been sanctioned by the Anekal Planning Authority vide No. LAO/05/16-17, dated 18/06/2020 and Building Plan sanctioned by the Anekal Planning Authority vide No.L.P. No.APA/CC/278/2020-21 dated 18/02/2021 for construction of Multistoried Apartment Complex consisting of 4 Towers with 662 units.</p></li>
                            <li><p style="text-align: justify;">The application to modify the Development Plan and Building Plan will be applied with the jurisdictional Planning/Municipal authority being the Anekal Planning Authority, after completion of due process and obtaining NOC from the Authority.</p></li>
                            
